Lab Objective

Change the EC2 instance:

nautilus-ec2

From:

t2.micro

To:

t2.nano

And ensure:

Instance State = Running
Status Checks = OK
Step 1: Verify AWS Login
aws sts get-caller-identity

Expected:

{
  "Account": "127822742629",
  "Arn": "arn:aws:iam::xxxxxxxx:user/kk_labs_user"
}
Step 2: Find the Instance
aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --filters "Name=tag:Name,Values=nautilus-ec2" \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].[InstanceId,State.Name,InstanceType]" \
  --output table

Example:

-----------------------------------------------
| Instance ID         | State   | Type        |
+---------------------+---------+-------------+
| i-04b9ed6a6c8fdba67 | running | t2.micro    |
-----------------------------------------------
Step 3: Check EC2 Status Checks
Why?

AWS performs:

System Status Check
Instance Status Check

Both must be ok.

Check:

aws ec2 describe-instance-status \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --output table

Possible output:

InstanceStatus : initializing
SystemStatus   : initializing

Wait until healthy:

aws ec2 wait instance-status-ok \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1

Verify again:

InstanceStatus : ok
SystemStatus   : ok
Step 4: Stop the Instance

AWS does not allow instance type changes on a running instance.

Stop:

aws ec2 stop-instances \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1

Wait:

aws ec2 wait instance-stopped \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1
Step 5: Change Instance Type

Change:

t2.micro → t2.nano

Command:

aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute \
  --instance-id <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --instance-type '{"Value":"t2.nano"}' \
  --region us-east-1

Verify:

aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].InstanceType" \
  --output text

Expected:

t2.nano
Step 6: Start the Instance
aws ec2 start-instances \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1

Wait:

aws ec2 wait instance-running \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1
Step 7: Final Verification

Verify instance state and type:

aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].[State.Name,InstanceType]" \
  --output table

Expected:

--------------------------
| running | t2.nano      |
--------------------------

Verify health:

aws ec2 describe-instance-status \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID> \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --output table

Expected:

InstanceStatus : ok
SystemStatus   : ok
Important AWS Wait Commands
Wait until EC2 is healthy
aws ec2 wait instance-status-ok \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID>
Wait until EC2 is stopped
aws ec2 wait instance-stopped \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID>
Wait until EC2 is running
aws ec2 wait instance-running \
  --instance-ids <INSTANCE_ID>
Interview Questions
Q1. Can you change an EC2 instance type while it is running?

No. The instance must be stopped first.

Q2. What is the purpose of modify-instance-attribute?

Used to modify EC2 instance attributes such as:

Instance type
Source/Destination check
User data
Q3. What are EC2 Status Checks?

AWS performs two checks:

System Status Check
Hypervisor
Network
Physical host
Instance Status Check
Operating system
Network configuration
Application startup
Q4. What does aws ec2 wait instance-status-ok do?

It waits until:

SystemStatus = ok
InstanceStatus = ok

before returning control to the terminal.

KodeKloud Exam Shortcut
INSTANCE_ID=$(aws ec2 describe-instances \
--filters "Name=tag:Name,Values=nautilus-ec2" \
--query "Reservations[].Instances[].InstanceId" \
--output text)

aws ec2 wait instance-status-ok --instance-ids $INSTANCE_ID

aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-ids $INSTANCE_ID

aws ec2 wait instance-stopped --instance-ids $INSTANCE_ID

aws ec2 modify-instance-attribute \
--instance-id $INSTANCE_ID \
--instance-type '{"Value":"t2.nano"}'

aws ec2 start-instances --instance-ids $INSTANCE_ID

aws ec2 wait instance-running --instance-ids $INSTANCE_ID
Memory Trick

Find → Check Health → Stop → Modify → Start → Verify

1. Find Instance
2. Wait for Status OK
3. Stop Instance
4. Change Type
5. Start Instance
6. Verify Running + OK
